  "texts": [
    "For training the model, most of the studies were conducted using paired datasets (where the images from both the modalities are given as input to learn the features) and very few studies used unpaired datasets.",
    "Some studies also compared the results on paired datasets over unpaired datasets (29, 60, 71, 72).",
    "Most commonly used networks were 2D networks, where 3D images were sliced into 2D images for training the network.",
    "Multiple configurations were also investigated in some studies (40, 73) described in this review.",
    "The most popular architecture for the image synthesis was Generative Adversarial Network (GAN), followed by U-Net and other Convolution Neural Networks (CNN)."
  ],
